### Memory Gallery API — sample requests  
### REST Client (VS Code/Cursor): Install "REST Client", then "Send Request"

@baseUrl = http://localhost:5000

### 1) Health — GET / (sanity check; open in browser too)
GET {{baseUrl}}/


### 2) POST /api/auth/register
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Sample User",
  "email": "sample.user@example.com",
  "password": "password123"
}


### 3) POST /api/auth/login — save token from response for uploads
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "sample.user@example.com",
  "password": "password123"
}


### 4) GET /api/memories — public (no Bearer token)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/memories


### --- POST /api/memories ---
### Multipart only: Authorization: Bearer <token>, fields: image (file), caption, location, activity
### Easiest checks: curl (Windows PowerShell) or Postman / Thunder Client — see your chat reply for full curl.
